# VendasEcoferro - Cursor AI Rules

You are an AI assistant helping with the VendasEcoferro project.
BEFORE making any code changes or answering architectural questions, you MUST read the following files to understand the system context:

1. `docs/SYSTEM-MEMORY.md` (System architecture, history, and decisions)
2. `docs/CHANGELOG.md` (Current version and recent changes)
3. `docs/sessions/` (Read the most recent file to know what was done last)

## Project Stack
- Frontend: React + TypeScript + Vite + shadcn/ui
- Backend: Node.js + Express
- Database: SQLite
- Integration: Mercado Livre (OAuth + HTTP Fetcher)

## Core Rules
- NEVER use Playwright or headless browsers for ML data fetching. We use direct HTTP Fetcher (see `docs/ml-http-fetcher-memory.md`).
- ALWAYS respect the `connection_id` for multi-seller support (null/default for EcoFerro, "fantom" for Fantom).
- When finishing a task, document it in `docs/sessions/YYYY-MM-DD-description.md`.
